#

Bourbon-Glazed Salmon with Garlic Mashed Potatoes and Steamed Asparagus

$25
600 kcal
Difficulty: 30%

Allergens:

FishDairy

Dietary Tags:

Gluten-FreeHigh-Protein

Tags:

DinnerGourmetAmerican Cuisine

Description

A succulent salmon fillet glazed with a sweet and tangy bourbon sauce, paired with creamy garlic mashed potatoes and fresh, crisp asparagus.

Ingredients

  • Salmon fillet: 4 (6 oz) pieces
  • Bourbon: 1/4 cup
  • Brown sugar: 2 tablespoons
  • Soy sauce: 2 tablespoons
  • Dijon mustard: 1 tablespoon
  • Garlic: 3 cloves, minced
  • Olive oil: 2 tablespoons
  • Asparagus: 1 pound
  • Potatoes: 2 pounds, peeled and cut into chunks
  • Butter: 4 tablespoons
  • Heavy cream: 1/2 cup
  • Salt: to taste
  • Black pepper: to taste
